2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper discusses learning feature representations and embedding them onto a hyperspace for discriminative analysis, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
3. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper evaluates the proposed methodology in the context of retrieval tasks, which is a sub-domain of information retrieval. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses classification and retrieval tasks, which are common in multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper proposes a methodology for embedding feature representations onto a metric space, which is relevant to natural language processing and computational linguistics.
